<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Projects shall be eligible if they are financed by the Member States or by regional or local authorities or by bodies working within an administrative or legal framework which makes them equivalent to public entities, in particular public or private enterprises which run public services or services in the public interest. </inglise>
<eesti> Projektid on abik&otilde;lblikud, kui neid rahastavad liikmesriigid v&otilde;i piirkondlikud v&otilde;i kohalikud ametiasutused v&otilde;i asutused, mille t&ouml;&ouml; toimub sellises haldus- v&otilde;i &otilde;iguslikus raamistikus, mille t&otilde;ttu neid loetakse riigiasutustega v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rseteks - need on eelk&otilde;ige riiklikud v&otilde;i eraettev&otilde;tted, mis pakuvad avalikke teenuseid v&otilde;i &uuml;ldistes huvides olevaid teenuseid. </eesti>
<inglise> A project shall be considered to be financed by the Member State when it is implemented and directly financed by a public authority or receives public aid or aid out of public resources, in whatever form, granted by a national, regional or local body. </inglise>
